-- Carney Says Canada to Remain Vigilant on Household Debt
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-01-23T16:33:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-23/carney-says-canada-to-remain-vigilant-on-household-debt-1-.html
Bank of Canada Governor Mark Carney
said the central bank will remain vigilant on household debt
levels.  Carney, speaking to reporters today in Ottawa, said the
central bank will make it clear if it takes measures to counter
household imbalances. Carney said there have been encouraging
signs that households are heeding warnings about debt levels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
